  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for absolute hemolysis predictions; however, the supporting validation activity was carried out as a high-fidelity numerical simulation whose results are argued in the narrative to be 'equivalent in evidentiary value' to bench-top experimental data. The structured activityType field records numerical-simulation, creating an inference-method mismatch with the requirement. Decision recorded as Accepted based on the narrative argument, masking the structural gap.",
