    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the submission on the basis that the inter-code numerical cross-check between Fluent and OpenFOAM, combined with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, provides sufficient confidence in the absolute hemolysis predictions. The team noted that the independent solver agreement within 4.2% RMS is argued by the submitter to be 'as good as' experimental bench data given the difficulty of in-vitro hemolysis measurement uncertainty (typically 15-20% CV). The requirement for experimental-validation was recorded as satisfied by the numerical-simulation activity under this argument. No formal substitution or equivalence determination was documented in the structured fields.",
